Hong Kong Jan.-July Yuan Trade Settlements 953 Billion Yuan

-- B y   S o p h i e   L e u n g
-- 
2011-09-15T09:30:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/hong-kong-jan-july-yuan-trade-settlements-953-billion-yuan.html
Yuan-denominated trade settlements
through  Hong Kong  banks reached 953 billion yuan in the period
January through July,  Donald Tsang , the city’s chief executive,
said in
Edinburgh, according to an official transcript.  Hong Kong accounted for more than 80 percent of all cross-
border trade settled in the Chinese currency, Tsang said. The
chief executive hopes to see Scottish companies selling shares
in Hong Kong “soon,” according to the transcript.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sophie Leung in Hong Kong at 
 sleung59@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Panckhurst at 
 ppanckhurst@bloomberg.net  